
// This Hyperlambda code logs an error message when an issue occurs during an OpenAI invocation. It uses the [log.error] slot to log the error, retrieving the error message from the HTTP POST response using [message], captures the status code with [status], and converts the error object to a Hyperlambda string with [error] using [lambda2hyper].
log.error:Something went wrong while invoking OpenAI
   message:x:@http.post/*/content/*/error/*/message
   status:x:@http.post
   error:x:@lambda2hyper
